# Config Safety Rules

## Secrets
- Never commit real `automation.yaml` (gitignored).
- Only `automation.example.yaml` with placeholder paths belongs in source control.
- Auth tokens must be empty or absent in example configs.

## Validation
- All config changes must pass Pydantic validation before apply.
- Cross-reference checks: playlist IDs in slots must exist in playlists list.
- Invalid config reload must be rejected; last known good config continues.

## Schema Evolution
- New fields must have sensible defaults so existing configs keep working.
- Never silently change the meaning of an existing field.
- Document new config sections in the example YAML with inline comments.

## Feature Flags
- Every new capability must be gated behind `config.features`.
- Flags default to `false` for new features until stable.
